claim.claim-text:
1. A system comprising:
a network device disposed at a site;
a mobile application stored within each of a first mobile device and a second mobile device and each configured to individually alter the network device at the site;
a processor configured to generate control action data in response to a comparison of a location of the first mobile device relative to the site as well as a location of the second mobile device relative to the site;
the processor further configured to alter an operating condition of the network device in response to the control action data reflecting the comparison;
wherein the network device includes a wireless thermostat responsive to the control action data being communicated to the network device;
a first user profile associated with the first mobile device, wherein the first user profile includes information to alter an operating condition of the network device according to a preference of a first user; and
a second user profile associated with the second mobile device, wherein the second user profile includes information to alter an operating condition of the network device according to a preference of a second user.

2. The system of claim 1, further comprising a remote server configured to:
receive a location based input from the first mobile device;
detect the first user profile of the first mobile device and the second user profile of the second mobile device;
determine whether to alter the network device in response to the location based input and the first user profile of the first mobile device and the second user profile of the second mobile device.

4. The system of claim 2, further comprising:
wherein the first user profile of the first mobile device includes an enabled proximity setting;
wherein the second user profile of the second mobile device includes an enabled proximity setting;
wherein the location based input is a first distance away from the site;
wherein a location of the second mobile device is greater than the location of the first mobile device;
wherein a user preference of the second mobile device is used to initiate altering an operating condition at the site; and
wherein a user preference of the first mobile device is not used to initiate an altering of the operating condition at the site.

9. A method comprising:
detecting an availability of a network device disposed at a site;
detecting a location of a first mobile device associated with the site;
detecting a location of a second mobile device associated with the site;
initiating communication of a location based input of the first mobile device to a network location configured to compare the location based input of the first mobile device to a location based input of the second mobile device;
comparing the location of the first mobile device and the location of the second mobile device relative to the site;
initiating a communication of a control action data in response to detecting the location of the first mobile device and the second mobile device being disposed away from the site;
altering the network device using the control action data;
receiving a communication from a network location indicating that an operating condition of the network device has been altered; and
updating the operating condition at the first mobile device.

12. The method of claim 9, further comprising:
detecting a first travel distance setting of the first mobile device;
detecting a second travel distance setting of the second mobile device, wherein the second travel distance setting is different than the first travel distance setting;
using the first travel distance setting of the first mobile device and a current location of the first mobile device to initiate the communication; and
using the second travel distance setting of the second mobile device and a current location of the second mobile device to initiate the communication.

16. A method comprising:
identifying a first mobile device with a site having a network device;
identifying a second mobile device with the site;
detecting an enabled proximity setting of the first mobile device;
detecting location information of the first mobile device in response to the enabled proximity setting of the first mobile device;
detecting an enabled proximity setting of the second mobile device;
detecting location information of the second mobile device in response to the enabled proximity setting of the second mobile device;
comparing location information of the first mobile device to location information of the second mobile device; and
initiating altering an operating condition of the network device in response to the comparison of the location information of the first mobile device to the location information of the second mobile device.

18. The method of claim 17, further comprising:
detecting the first mobile device being disposed at the site;
detecting the first mobile device moving away from the site;
enabling the proximity setting of the first mobile device in response to detecting the first mobile device moving away from the site; and
altering the operating condition of the network device in response to the first mobile device being disposed at a distance from the site.
